Risk Management Plan

Manteno Dawn Foods Products, Inc.



I.    Introduction

A Risk Management Program has been implemented at the Manteno Dawn Foods Products, Inc. (Manteno Dawn Foods) facility located at 1340 Sycamore Street in Manteno, Illinois for the reduction of accidental releases of hazardous materials. This updated Risk Management Plan (RMP) summarizes the management, administrative, procedural, and technological controls that work together to minimize the risk to site personnel, contractors, visitors, and the community and environment at large of hazardous chemical releases. The RMP is organized to correspond with specific U.S. Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) RMP, Program 3 of 40 CFR 68, definitions and requirements of Subpart G, including: 

?    Introduction;

?    Manteno Dawn Foods policies to protect health, environment, and safety;

?    Facility identification and regulated substances covered processes;

?    Hazard Assessment;

?    Prevention Program;

?    Five-Year Accident History;

?    Emergency Response Plan; 

?    Emergency Communications;

?    Spill Reporting / Environmental Release Procedures;

?    Planned changes to improve safety; and

?    Management Program



II.    Manteno Dawn Foods Policies to Protect Health, Environment, and Safety

Risk management and safety are important concerns at Manteno Dawn Foods; this RMP formalizes and documents these activities. Manteno Dawn Foods is committed to conducting its operations in a safe and responsible manner and to reducing risks to human health and to the environment. It is Manteno Dawn Foods' policy to comply with all applicable federal, state, and local rules and regulations.



This RMP has identified potential hazards and has taken steps to design and maintain a safe facility in order to prevent releases, and minimize the consequences of accidental releases, which could occur. RMP addresses potentially catastrophic chemical releases that could result in immediate harm and acute health effects to offsite receptors
